FBIS4-53372 "dreas097_i_94001" FBIS-EAS-94-097 Daily Report 18 May 1994 Cambodia Continued Exchange of Messages on Peace Talks Continued Exchange of Messages on Peace Talks Sihanouk Message to Khieu Samphan BK1805164494 Phnom Penh National Radio of Cambodia Network in Cambodian 1300 GMT 18 May 94 BK1805164494 Phnom Penh National Radio of Cambodia Network in Cambodian 1300 GMT 18 May 94 Cambodian BFN [Text] His Majesty Norodom Sihanouk Varaman, king of Cambodia, sent a message to His Excellency Khieu Samphan, chairman of the Party of Democratic Kampuchea [PDK] on 18 May. The message reads as follows: Excellency, I would like to deeply thank you for sending me a message in the name of the PDK to support my suggestion of a roundtable at my Chhanghsu-on residence near Pyongyang. I ask Your Excellency to give me a very clear and specific answer to the following question: Will Your Excellency attend the roundtable for national reconciliation and peace in Cambodia, that is, the roundtable which will be held at Chhanghsu-on on 27 May? With my deepest thanks, Excellency, please accept my highest regards. [Signed] Norodom Sihanouk
